Auto-Mapping Radius Configuration Guide for Juniper BNG
This documentation provides a comprehensive, step-by-step guide to setting up and maintaining an automated rate-limiting system between DMA Billing (MariaDB/MySQL) and a Juniper BNG using FreeRADIUS (radusergroup & radgroupreply).
________________
1. System Architecture Flow
This integration ensures zero-maintenance synchronization between billing packages and network bandwidth limits:
1. Billing Web Admin Panel: You create/update a user and assign them a package (e.g., 15Mbps-JunOS).
2. Database Trigger: A custom trigger automatically runs on the rm_users table upon any INSERT or UPDATE.
3. Dynamic Group Mapping: The trigger queries the billing system's service table (rm_services), resolves the exact package name assigned to the user, and dynamically inserts/updates this group name in the radusergroup table.
4. Juniper Client Auth: When the subscriber connects via PPPoE, FreeRADIUS fetches the attributes mapped to that package name from radgroupreply and delivers the correct rate-limiting attribute (ERX-Service-Activate:1) to the BNG.
________________
2. One-Time Database Setup (Smart Triggers)
Run these queries once on your MariaDB/MySQL database (radius). This setup is fully dynamic and does not need to be updated when you add new packages in the future.

mysql -u root -p
Enter Your Password:


Copy And Paste The Following:

-- --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
